OL,3,CCotherstone residents transform Old
OL,4,CChapel into thriving community business
OL,6,FResidents in a County Durham village,
OL,7,Fwho had seen their only shop and post
OL,8,Foffice close five years ago, have
OL,9,Fworked together to set up a new
OL,10,Fcommunity owned business at the old
OL,11,FMethodist chapel.
OL,13,FThe Cotherstone Old Chapel Project has
OL,14,Ftransformed the chapel into a
OL,15,Fcommunity hub, providing both
OL,16,Fresidents and tourists with a place to
OL,17,Fmeet, chat, buy groceries and eat.
